title: For Sale:  Ithaca Flues No. 2 Grade 12ga 26" SxS Shotgun
postcontent: This auction is for a really nice Ithaca Flues No.2 Grade Side by Side Double Barrel Shotgun that I have used for many years as a good skeet/trap gun. It weighs only 7 lbs. The No.2 grade is several steps above the common field grade guns and has lots of beautifully detailed factory engraving, even on the screw heads, and features richly grained, high quality wood. This gun has SN#349364, which indicates it was made in 1921. It is 12 Gauge with 26" Barrels, left is choked full, right is cylinder bore, and the length of pull is 13 3/4" with an early vintage Pachmayr White Line rubber pad on the butt. It has an automatic safety, double triggers and extractors. The serial numbers all match. The metal finish appears to be all original, with the rust bluing on the barrels at around 90%, while a substantial amount of original case colors remains on the receiver with some protected areas and the bottom looking really bright. The deluxe tiger striped stock is in great shape with no cracks and sharp checkering, while the forearm has some wear and scuffs, but is still in good shape with a deluxe ebony insert at the front. The left barrel has a very slight ding about 4" from the muzzle (also in a pic). Bores are mint, and the gun is mechanically sound and locks up nice and tight. I've tried to describe the gun accurately, with plenty of detailed photos, but please email me if you have questions. Thanks for looking, and good luck in bidding! This gun ships to a C&R or FFL holders, and shipping is $25, extra for Alaska or Hawaii. Payment can be via Western Union, USPS Money Orders/Certified Checks and personal checks. Please note that for personal checks gun will not ship until check clears. Please ensure that the item(s) you are bidding on are legal in the state you reside in.

title: For Sale:  Ithaca Flues No. 2 Grade 12ga 26" SxS Shotgun
postcontent: This auction is for a really nice Ithaca Flues No.2 Grade Side by Side Double Barrel Shotgun that I have used for many years as a good skeet/trap gun. It weighs only 7 lbs. The No.2 grade is several steps above the common field grade guns and has lots of beautifully detailed factory engraving, even on the screw heads, and features richly grained, high quality wood. This gun has SN#349364, which indicates it was made in 1921. It is 12 Gauge with 26" Barrels, left is choked full, right is cylinder bore, and the length of pull is 13 3/4" with an early vintage Pachmayr White Line rubber pad on the butt. It has an automatic safety, double triggers and extractors. The serial numbers all match. The metal finish appears to be all original, with the rust bluing on the barrels at around 90%, while a substantial amount of original case colors remains on the receiver with some protected areas and the bottom looking really bright. The deluxe tiger striped stock is in great shape with no cracks and sharp checkering, while the forearm has some wear and scuffs, but is still in good shape with a deluxe ebony insert at the front. The left barrel has a very slight ding about 4" from the muzzle (also in a pic). Bores are mint, and the gun is mechanically sound and locks up nice and tight. I've tried to describe the gun accurately, with plenty of detailed photos, but please email me if you have questions. Thanks for looking, and good luck in bidding! This gun ships to a C&R or FFL holders, and shipping is $25, extra for Alaska or Hawaii. Payment can be via Western Union, USPS Money Orders/Certified Checks and personal checks. Please note that for personal checks gun will not ship until check clears. Please ensure that the item(s) you are bidding on are legal in the state you reside in.

For rapid target acquisition, it features a receiver-mounted, fully adjustable XS® Ghost Ring Sight rail with removable white bead front sight - Picatinny-style rail accepts optics and sight systems as well. This gun packs a full 7 rounds of 2 3/4" or 3" 12-gauge firepower with the factory-installed 2-shot extension. It also includes a drilled and tapped receiver and sling swivel stud.
